      <gmd:abstract>
        <gco:CharacterString>
          The EMO database compiles Eocene marine ostracode records from multiple sources including the Paleobiology Database (PBDB), World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS), online publications, non-digital publication and primary data datasets. The database provides standardized taxonomic, spatial, and ecological information to support paleobiological, paleoecological and macroevolutionary analyses.
        </gco:CharacterString>
      </gmd:abstract>

